            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} reports no previous cancer diagnosis and no prior breast surgery. She sought evaluation after personally detecting a new breast lump and later noticing nipple discharge and local irritation with a feeling of swelling [SNOMED:C50.9]. She has not had recent trauma to the breast and did not present with symptoms suggesting another cause from the provided evidence. \n\nHer background history is otherwise notable for common age-appropriate chronic disease screening and routine primary care follow-up, but no major prior hospitalizations are reported. She is a nonsmoker by history, drinks alcohol only occasionally, and remains functionally independent. She lives with family support and says the emotional stress of awaiting answers has been more difficult than the physical discomfort from the breast changes [SNOMED:C50.9]."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
